<div class="block-rich_text"><h4 data-block-key="hakfj">Uncover captivating stories of art on the Cornish Coast</h4><p data-block-key="7qjt9">Overlooking the Atlantic Ocean, Tate St Ives showcases work by artists including <a href="https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/dame-barbara-hepworth-1274">Barbara Hepworth</a>, <a href="https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/marlow-moss-1671">Marlow Moss</a>, <a href="https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/naum-gabo-1137">Naum Gabo</a> and <a href="https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/patrick-heron-1278">Patrick Heron</a>, whose captivating works have brought international attention to St Ives and West Cornwall. Alongside displays from the Tate collection, the gallery presents modern and contemporary art from around the world through a dynamic exhibitions programme.</p></div>
<div class="block-rich_text"><h4 data-block-key="wm8a7">Discover visual artist Outi Pieski’s exploration of identity, culture and environment</h4><p data-block-key="fmvff"><a href="https://www.tate.org.uk/whats-on/tate-st-ives/outi-pieski">Outi Pieski</a> is a Sámi visual artist based in Ohcejohka (Utsjoki), Finland. This will be her first large-scale exhibition in the UK.</p><p data-block-key="7k7sb">Pieski&#x27;s paintings and installations explore several themes, including the culture and identity of the Sámi people – who live in the region of Sápmi, which now includes the northern part of Scandinavia and Kola peninsula in Russia.</p><p data-block-key="4ofrg">Book entry until 6 May</p></div>
<div class="block-cta_row">
<div class="btn-row btn-row--align__left">
    
        
    <a href="https://shop.tate.org.uk/ticket/date?cgid=325473" class="btn btn--type__primary">
        <i class="btn__icon icon--arrow-right"></i>
        <span class="btn__text">Book entry</span>
    </a>


    
</div>
</div>
<div class="block-rich_text"><p data-block-key="5pm9n">Some of our galleries are closed 7 – 24 May as we prepare for the new exhibition by Beatriz Milhazes and a Mark Rothko display. Gallery admission is reduced to reflect this:</p><p data-block-key="5ev56">Adults £10 or £9 without donation. Concessions £9 or £8 without donation.</p><p data-block-key="3mj40">Book entry for 7 – 24 May</p></div>
<div class="block-cta_row">
<div class="btn-row btn-row--align__left">
    
        
    <a href="https://shop.tate.org.uk/ticket/date?cgid=340932" class="btn btn--type__primary">
        <i class="btn__icon icon--arrow-right"></i>
        <span class="btn__text">Book entry</span>
    </a>


    
</div>
</div>
<div class="block-rich_text"><p data-block-key="qcx38">Coming soon: <a href="https://www.tate.org.uk/whats-on/tate-st-ives/beatriz-milhazes-maresias">Beatriz Milhazes: Maresias</a></p><p data-block-key="3quqa">Tate St Ives presents a retrospective of the work of artist <a href="https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/beatriz-milhazes-8358">Beatriz Milhazes</a>, who is known for intensely colourful, large-scale abstract canvases. The exhibition traces the evolution of her artistic approach over the past four decades.</p><p data-block-key="f9dr6">Book entry from 25 May</p></div>
<div class="block-cta_row">
<div class="btn-row btn-row--align__left">
    
        
